Police detectives have arrested the former Sports Cabinet Secretary Rashid Echesa. The details regarding his arrest is yet to be confirmed. Echesa was arrested on Thursday and taken to the DCI Headquarters located in Kiambu Road. His vehicles have also been impounded including a Range Rover. Last year, Echesa blamed opposition leader Raila Odinga for his sacking. Echesa said his tough stance against privatisation of state-owned sugar factories and his unwavering support for Deputy President William Ruto’s 2022 bid contributed to is removal on March 1, 2019. Echesa was fired in March 2019 by president Uhuru Kenyatta from sports docket replacing him with the current CS Ambassador Amina Mohammed. More to follow